## 4. Parallax Placement Recommendations

> [!NOTE]
> These are ordered from highest brand impact to lowest. Implementation priority is marked.

---

### 🔴 Priority 1 — Hero: Background Layer Depth Parallax

**Where:** Behind the 3D video carousel in `Hero.tsx`

**Effect:** Add 2–3 absolutely-positioned ambient layers (subtle noise/grain texture, a soft gold orb gradient, floating particle dots) that move at fractions of the scroll speed.

| Layer | Speed Multiplier | Content |
|---|---|---|
| Background noise texture | `0.1x` | Existing noise overlay, currently static |
| Gold radial glow | `0.2x` | A `bg-accent/5` circle that drifts up |
| Floating mark/emblem | `0.3x` | Small "MONARCH" wordmark or geometric icon |

**Code approach:**
```tsx
// In Hero.tsx — useScroll + useTransform (Framer Motion)
const { scrollY } = useScroll();
const glowY = useTransform(scrollY, [0, 500], [0, -80]);
const noiseY = useTransform(scrollY, [0, 500], [0, -20]);

// Apply via motion.div style={{ y: glowY }}
```

**Brand Rationale:** The hero sets the world. If it's flat and static behind the carousel, users don't feel "pulled in." Adding Z-depth to the background transforms the hero from a "header" into a **space you enter**. This is exactly what Festivent does with its festival world.

